Reasoning: The paper deals with a modal logic system that combines classical and intuitionistic logic, and focuses on epistemic extensions and completeness w.r.t. algebraic semantics. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Logic and Verification (cs.LG), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). However, since the paper primarily deals with modal logic and epistemic extensions, cs.LO is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.LG.
